When we first got swerve (2022 off season) we wrote our own code which works pretty well. For the next season, we are looking to up our odometry level and one of the features I saw in the CTRE swerve code is multi thread and synced odometry.

Have anyone tried using it? How was your experience? And would you recommend it?

Yes. Great. Yes.

Also the setup of the swerve drive took a painful process that required a good amount of skill and care and made it simple.

That isn’t to say your bot is going to drive like 1690’s out of the box (still tons of opportunity to add and improve things, not with the CTRE library but with specific drivetrain and its usage) but having a driving swerve day 1 sure is a nice place to start.

10/10 recommend

Also change your default current limits when you do generate it

We already have a pretty solid swerve code. Our main reason that we might change to CTRE is the odometry. Sure, we can write thread time synced odometry there but it will take time and resources. Dose the ctre odometry works well for you? Have you tried using the wpi pose estimator class (what we are currently using)?
